 Business Briefs
																								 Mumbai, Oct. 13: Indias foreign exchange reserves crossed $250 billion for the first time during the week ended October 5. Surging inflows of $3.56 billion increased the reserves to $251.33 billion. The reserves increased to $247.76 billion because of a $11.87-billion inflow during the week ended September 28. Foreign currency assets increased $3.56 billion to $243.52 billion against $239.95 billion a week before, the Reserve Bank data said. During the week, gold reserves and special drawing rights remained static at $7.36 billion and $2 million, respectively.																								 Calcutta, Oct. 13: Haldia Petrochemicals is planning to diversify its polymer business by adding new products, besides expanding its capacity. The proposals will be placed before the board for approval by the end of this year.
